  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate whether there are quantifiable differences in
      walking stability, as measured by the acceleration of the trunk or the variation in step
      length, between people with unilateral below-knee amputations from vascular reasons or from
      trauma reasons.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
